        <headline>Heat Advisory issued July 28 at 2:11PM CDT until July 29 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...For the Extreme Heat Warning today, dangerously hot
conditions with heat index values up to 115. For the Heat Advisory
on Tuesday, heat index values up to 105 expected.

* WHERE...Portions of west central Illinois, southeast Iowa, and
northeast Missouri.

* WHEN...For the Extreme Heat Warning, until 8 PM CDT this evening.
For the Heat Advisory, from noon to 8 PM CDT Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Heat related illnesses increase significantly during
extreme heat and high humidity events. Hot temperatures and high
humidity may cause heat illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.

Do not leave young children and pets in unattended vehicles. Car
interiors will reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.</instruction>
